Google Maps API easy to use with GVMaps jQuery Plugin

Last Release

		Version 0.93

Features

GVMaps works with Google Maps API Version 3.

As a html property you can:

    Select map type between normal, sattellite or hybrid. Eg.:

    <div id="map" data-mapType="hybrid"></div>

    Set latitude, longitude and zoom level. Eg.:

    <div id="map" data-latitude="41.875696" data-longitude="-87.624207" data-zoom="11"></div>

    Set query to search any place at map like this:

    <div id="map" data-query="Av. Dr. Cardoso de Mello, S達o Paulo - SP" data-zoom="15"></div>

    Set route like this:

    <div id="map" data-from="Av. Dr. Cardoso de Mello, S達o Paulo - SP" data-to="Av. Ibirapuera, S達o Paulo - SP"></div>

Using javascript plugin function you can:

    Set query to search any place at map like this:

    $('#map').gvmap().query('Santos - SP, Brazil')

    Trace route like this:

    $('#map').gvmap().route('Santos - SP, Brazil', 'S達o Paulo - SP, Brazil')

    Change map position at runtime:

    $('#map').gvmap().latLng(-23.961392, -46.391745)

More Examples

    Examples can be found at GVMaps Project Repository
